[Method]
AddColumns
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method adds columns to a ListView control with the Report style set. The width, justification, and optional image from the image list can or must be specified for each column.
\par \par The column justification is to be set using:
\par 0	Left (default)
\par 1	Center
\par 2	Right
\par \par \b Please Note:\b0 \par Due to limitations in the ListView control, column 0 is always left justified and cannot be changed.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab sColText
[as String]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nJustification
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nColWidth
[as Integer]
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 nImageListIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]


[Method]
AddItem (For Report Style)
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method adds a new item to the end of a ListView control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list. Use \cf1 dcl_ListView_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 nImageIndex ...
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...
[as String]
[End List]


[Method]
AddItem
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method adds a new item to the end of a ListView control. 
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 nImageIndex ...
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]


