[Desc]
This method inserts a new item anywhere in a ListView control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list.  Use \cf2 dcl_ListView_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nInsertRowIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
\par\tab nImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional} \i0 sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...
[as String]
[End List]


