[Method]
SortTextItems
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method will sort the columns in ascending or descending order, based on the column index provided. This method will not keep track of which column was sorted as ascending or descending, this is up to you.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nColIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab bAscending
[as Integer, T or Nil] (1 or T = Ascending, 0 or Nil = Descending) 


[Method]
SortNumericItems
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method will sort the columns in ascending or descending order using a numeric comparison, based on the column index provided. This method will not keep track of which column was sorted as ascending or descending, this is up to you.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nColIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab bAscending
[as Integer, T or Nil] (1 or T = Ascending, 0 or Nil = Descending) 


[Method]
StartLabelEdit
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method will force the label of an item to show the edit box, so the user may rename the text content of that item.  When using this method on a ListView control with the Report style setting only the item in the first column may be edited.  This method will not start the editing process if the EditLabel property of the control is set to False. This method is not available for BlockList controls.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>
\par\tab nItemIndex
[as Integer]


[Method]
CancelLabelEdit
[Prefix]
dcl_ListView_
[Desc]
This method will cancel the label editing of an item, so the user may not rename the text content of that item. This is useful when you wish to ensure that some items may be edited while others may not.  This method is not available for BlockList controls.
[Arguments]
<CONTROL>

[End of File]
